<TEXT>
A strike by ground crew workers at Leonardo Da Vinci 
airport on Sunday forced cancellation of some of Alitalias 
domestic and international flights 
Employees walked off the job at 7 am and said they would stay 
out until midnight to protest the unexpected suspension of 
negotiations on a new contract 
Labor leaders representing ground crews and pilots told Italian 
newspapers they will stage periodic strikes at Italian airports 
until Feb 29 Strikers want to force Alitalia the national flag 
carrier to meet their demands for shorter hours and higher pay 
Travelers in Italy may face other transportation problems near 
the end of the month when national train strikes are planned 
Railroad workers plan strikes Feb 26 and Feb 2829 
</TEXT>
